hand as an autotelic pursuit of truth. On the other hand, it also keeps the practical benefit of new knowledge in its sights. David Kaldewey reconstructs the origin and significance of this dual goal by means of historical-sociological semantic analysis. He shows how both objectives condense among a variety of autonomy and practice discourses. The tension between these discourses reveals itself from a differentiation theoretical perspective as constitutive of the dynamics of modern science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAutonomie. 4aDifferenzierungstheorie. 4aPraxis. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aSystemtheorie. 4aUniversität. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftssoziologie. 4aWissenssoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aScience.  aSociological Theory.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology.  aSystems Theory.  aUniversity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2010-2013z9783110370713oZDB-23-TSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839425657zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839425657zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839425657/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2013  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013  aZDB-23-TSWc2010d2013